description.plain:
“Hotel” is Kita’s first song to be certified Gold by ARIA, but its success is something simultaneously heartwarming and bittersweet.



The song was inspired by Kita’s sister, Tash, who passed away from cancer at the age of 21. Tash was the one who taught Kita how to play the guitar, igniting her music career.

“I totally feel she is looking out for this song; it’s the only one of mine I can listen to. I had written so many songs about Tash but never felt I had the right words or it felt right because I found it so hard to talk about losing my sister, to the point I wouldn’t even tell people I had a sibling if they asked. Putting it into this lyric and melody was part of the healing process and now when people ask if I have a sibling, I tell them I have an angel sister.”
- Kita Alexander, for Daily Telegraph

WELCOME TO GENIUS' NOVEMBER 2019 SINGLES RELEASE CALENDAR!!!



For November 2019 album releases, visit this page



This page highlights the notable singles released in all genres throughout November 2019. Each song title includes a hyperlink to the corresponding lyric page.

HOW CAN YOU HELP?


Adding songs



If there’s a notable song you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you notice that any of the songs on this list haven’t been transcribed, go to the corresponding page and add in lyrics!


Updating dates



If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.
